'Show closing brace tag when folding code blocks for clarity',' Prerequisites x Can you reproduce the problem in safe mode https atom io docs latest hacking atom debugging check if the problem shows up in safe mode x Are you running the latest version of Atom https atom io docs latest hacking atom debugging update to the latest version x Did you check the debugging guide https atom io docs latest hacking atom debugging x Did you check the FAQs on Discuss https discuss atom io c faq x Are you reporting to the correct repository https github com atom atom blob master CONTRIBUTING md atom and packages x Did you perform a cursory search https github com issues q is 3Aissue user 3Aatom repo 3Aatom 2Felectron to see if your bug or enhancement is already reported For more information on how to write a good bug report https github com atom atom blob master CONTRIBUTING md how do i submit a good bug report or enhancement request https github com atom atom blob master CONTRIBUTING md how do i submit a good enhancement suggestion see the CONTRIBUTING guide Description Per some discussion on the Atom boards https discuss atom io t code folding close bracket 9997 there s some concession that folded blocks of code can often be difficult to parse and work around Here are some examples of the current behavior and a suggested change to make the fold easier to parse js Example code function console log Hello world console log How are you today How Atom currently handles folds within a given syntax Folding the function Atom JavaScript syntax function What I expect to happen to happen in a given syntax Folding the function Atom Plain Text syntax function Folding the function Sublime Text function A one line variation function And another example using HTML html Example code section p Hello world p section How Atom currently handles folds within a given syntax Folding the block Atom HTML syntax section What I expect to happen to happen in a given syntax Folding the block Atom Plain Text syntax section section Folding the block Sublime Text section section A one line variation section section The Atom Plain Text syntax and Sublime Text format is easier to parse because it s clear where the function block starts and stops It also makes wrapping a folded block with more code easier because you can see the beginning and end of the full statement The other problem with the current Atom folding method is indenting a folded function does not work properly JavaScript Example Indenting folded JavaScript in Atom https zippy gfycat com ExcellentMerryCoyote gif HTML Example Indenting folded HTML in Atom https zippy gfycat com FarTenseAdeliepenguin gif lee dohm suggested I provide some examples of other folds besides just the 1TBS https en wikipedia org wiki Indent style Variant 1TBS style I ve noted some proposals Stroustrup c Example class Vector public Vector int s elem new double s sz s double operator int i return elem i int size return sz private double elem lowast int sz Expected class Vector public private Allman js Example while x y something somethingelse Expected while x y Steps to Reproduce 1 Launch Atom 2 In the correct syntax not just Plain Text write a multiline indented function block 3 Collapse block 4 To replicate indentation issue Indent the folded one line block Versions Atom 1 5 4 apm 1 6 0 ',enhancement
